  <name>mdparser</name>
  <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
  <summary>Native CommonMark + GitHub Flavored Markdown parser for PHP</summary>
  <description>
mdparser is a native PHP extension that parses CommonMark and
GitHub-Flavored Markdown in C using an embedded copy of cmark-gfm. No
external runtime dependencies; the parser ships entirely inside the
extension .so.

Features:
- 100% CommonMark 0.31 spec conformance (652/652)
- GFM extensions: tables, strikethrough, task lists, autolinks, tagfilter
- Three output formats per parse: HTML, XML, AST (nested PHP arrays)
- Sourcepos support for every AST node
- Modern PHP 8.3+ OO API with a final readonly Options class

Typical usage:

    $parser = new MdParser\Parser();
    echo $parser->toHtml('# Hello');

    $parser = new MdParser\Parser(new MdParser\Options(
        smart: true,
        sourcepos: true,
        unsafe: false,
    ));
  </description>
